text: Hammerfest (; ) is a municipality in Finnmark county, Norway. The administrative center of the municipality is the town of Hammerfest. The municipality has an area of and a population of 11,274 people. The population density is low, with only 4.4 people per square kilometer (1.7/m²). The municipality is made up of three large islands and several small islands. Most of it is not connected to the mainland by road. Hammerfest was formed as a municipality in 1838. In 1992, it merged with the neighboring municipality of Sørøysund to form a larger municipality with the same name. In 2020, it became part of the newly formed Troms og Finnmark county. ==Related pages== *List of mayors in Norway that are elected until 2027 == References == Category:Municipalities of Finnmark
